	"description": "The fishermen of Bodega Bay, California shared this favorite, quick and easy recipe with my sister during a Fish Festival. It is one of the best chowders I've had, and my kids love it too! We top with bacon bits and a few shakes of hot sauce for a little spice. Enjoy!",
	"directions": [{
		"ordinal": 1,
		"displayValue": "In a large stockpot, melt 2 tablespoons butter over medium heat. Saute onions, mushrooms and celery in butter until tender.",
		"videoTimestamp": 24000
	}, {
		"ordinal": 2,
		"displayValue": "Add chicken stock and potatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.",
		"videoTimestamp": 51000
	}, {
		"ordinal": 3,
		"displayValue": "Add fish, and simmer another 10 minutes.",
		"videoTimestamp": 71000
	}, {
		"ordinal": 4,
		"displayValue": "Season to taste with Old Bay seasoning, salt and pepper. Mix together clam juice and flour until smooth; stir into soup. Remove from heat, and stir in evaporated milk. Serve.",
		"videoTimestamp": 101000
	}],
