		"rating": 4,
		"text": "I enjoyed this recipe, only changed a few things to make it a little healthier/lower fat.  I used red onion in place of the green ones and sauteed them in olive oil instead of butter.  I also used 1% milkfat cottage cheese in place of the ricotta.  This turned out very creamy and tasted very good.  I skipped covering the top of the enchiladas with cheese, so I only used 1 cup in the filling.  Didn't miss it!  I also used fresh spinach cooked down instead of frozen simply b/c I had it on hand and needed to cook it.  I will absolutely make this again.  ",
