		"reviewID": 2102498,
		"rating": 5,
		"text": "This is the same recipe I have used for years.  We love it. The only thing I do different is I use  2 1/2 tablespoons brown sugar instead of white sugar.  The same amount.   Try it you will like it.   My son makes excellent Bulgogi and egg rolls.   This is the recipe that we use.  We buy a good beef loin and freeze it.   That makes it easier to slice.   He slices it very thin and then we marinate.  We also use this marinade on chicken and pork.  It is delicious.",
